rComments: Really great prof, super straight forward. For our course he did modules posted online then once a week you would gather to go over everything and do breakout rooms. I did not attend most of the live lectures and still did fine, just kept up with the modules. 3 essays, the last on he made optional so I have no exam for that course!

Overall a good class. Readings and movies were relevant and interesting. He tries to incorporate breakout rooms, but from my experience it was mostly a place where ppl would catch up. I don't love how he makes us outline our papers but other than that he's great. Gave extensions on assignments when requested and ended up making the final optional

Overall a good class. The class materiel is interesting & the readings are pretty straight forward. I'm not a huge fan of his essay format, but you don't need to stress too much about following it to the T. He offered extensions if needed which I really appreciated & provided good feedback. Course work consits of 3 essays. 10 / 10 would recommend!

Literally one of the best profs I've ever had in uni, namely for one particular reason: HE'S SO CLEAR IN HIS EXPECTATIONS. He tells you /exactly/ what he wants and the more closely you follow it, the more you secure your solid A. Ofc youll have to work for it, but he makes it easier for you! TLDR; GR8 PROF, WANTS YOU TO SUCCEED. 10/10 A REAL GEM
